1
00:00:03,169 --> 00:00:05,710
(The Heirs)

2
00:00:20,629 --> 00:00:25,359
(The Heirs)

3
00:00:26,899 --> 00:00:29,100
(Episode 4)

4
00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:01,429
Cha Eun Sang. Stop right there.

5
00:01:27,590 --> 00:01:29,459
Have a safe trip.
Call me when you arrive.

6
00:01:34,629 --> 00:01:37,439
Why didn't you call me?
Didn't your friend tell you?

7
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:40,739
- He did.
- Then you should've called me.

8
00:01:41,769 --> 00:01:43,040
Are you going to Korea now?

9
00:01:44,180 --> 00:01:45,780
What did you want to say?

10
00:01:47,549 --> 00:01:49,250
Give me your number.

11
00:01:52,450 --> 00:01:53,519
What are you waiting for?

12
00:01:59,689 --> 00:02:00,930
"Thank you for everything."

13
00:02:01,689 --> 00:02:03,129
I thanked you.

14
00:02:03,859 --> 00:02:06,129
"Bye." I said goodbye.

15
00:02:06,599 --> 00:02:07,670
I did all I should do.

16
00:02:09,569 --> 00:02:12,569
So don't leave your fiancee alone
to ask something trivial like that.

17
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:05,960
Here's the declaration form.

18
00:03:22,139 --> 00:03:24,539
(Customs Declaration)

19
00:03:40,590 --> 00:03:41,590
What are you doing?

20
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:42,960
I'm waiting for you
to finish writing.

21
00:03:43,389 --> 00:03:44,400
Finish it first.

22
00:03:45,530 --> 00:03:46,560
What's the matter?

23
00:03:48,629 --> 00:03:50,000
I've thought about it.

24
00:03:50,300 --> 00:03:53,370
I got a sad premonition
that we'll meet again.

25
00:03:53,370 --> 00:03:54,770
That won't happen.

26
00:03:55,909 --> 00:03:58,139
You say that because
you don't know Kim Tan well.

27
00:03:59,580 --> 00:04:03,479
If that sad premonition comes true,
I think I'll want to see you first.

28
00:04:03,819 --> 00:04:05,349
But I don't know anything about you.

29
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:07,219
That's why.

30
00:04:07,349 --> 00:04:08,349
What do you mean?

31
00:04:08,349 --> 00:04:09,689
Let's say this is
how we introduced ourselves.

32
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,560
Hey.

33
00:04:16,329 --> 00:04:19,759
I'm sorry, but you cannot enter
unless you're in first class.

34
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:22,769
No, the girl who just walked in
took my declaration form.

35
00:04:22,769 --> 00:04:25,300
If you wait here, I'll check.

36
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:39,250
I'm sorry, but she said she didn't.

37
00:04:39,649 --> 00:04:40,850
What...

38
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,709
(Welcome back, my stepsister!)

39
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:34,509
If you're bored, go wash the dishes.

40
00:05:34,509 --> 00:05:36,540
You said you weren't coming.
Why did you come and bother me?

41
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:37,740
Did you help me not to?

42
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:40,879
You told your mom that you changed
the flight.

43
00:05:41,579 --> 00:05:42,879
Couldn't you just come back quietly?

44
00:05:42,879 --> 00:05:44,949
You shouldn't have lost to your dad.

45
00:05:48,589 --> 00:05:52,089
Unless you want to walk home,
let's go quietly. Without talking.

46
00:05:52,089 --> 00:05:55,329
I'll tell Mom that you came
to pick me up,

47
00:05:55,990 --> 00:05:57,060
so push it.

48
00:06:01,329 --> 00:06:02,370
Gosh.

49
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:49,310
You must be dying to know
how Tan's doing. He's doing well.

50
00:06:50,050 --> 00:06:52,050
Tan asked me how you are doing.

51
00:06:52,379 --> 00:06:55,189
I said you're still mean
and living very well.

52
00:06:55,449 --> 00:06:58,490
The fox is playing
because the tiger's away.

53
00:07:04,129 --> 00:07:05,930
- Stop the car.
- Yes, sir.

54
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,810
Have you ever thought about this?

55
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:18,509
Why is the tiger away?

56
00:07:19,509 --> 00:07:21,750
Maybe he just pretended
to be a tiger.

57
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:24,879
Maybe he ran away...

58
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,189
before people find out.

59
00:07:30,089 --> 00:07:31,959
- What do you...
- Goodbye.

60
00:08:39,789 --> 00:08:41,860
What? Where did everything go?

61
00:09:00,110 --> 00:09:01,309
Hey, Eun Sang.

62
00:09:03,210 --> 00:09:05,279
Ma'am. What happened?

63
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,519
Where is my mom?

64
00:09:06,620 --> 00:09:10,350
Your mom moved out.
She's working as a resident maid.

65
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:11,789
What?

66
00:09:14,090 --> 00:09:16,559
I'm sorry,
but can I borrow your phone?

67
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:24,500
The chairman is ill.
The mood in the house is down.

68
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:27,340
Sleep in the sauna tonight
and come tomorrow morning.

69
00:10:25,929 --> 00:10:29,429
I saw that you wore jeans
without socks last week.

70
00:10:30,070 --> 00:10:33,840
I know it's summer,
but I didn't like it.

71
00:10:34,870 --> 00:10:36,110
It won't happen again.

72
00:10:38,580 --> 00:10:41,809
But you're wearing a skirt today.

73
00:10:42,909 --> 00:10:45,220
You wore shorts the week before.

74
00:10:46,379 --> 00:10:47,620
Let me ask you again.

75
00:10:48,549 --> 00:10:52,789
While you're tutoring, please
avoid clothes that show your skin.

76
00:10:53,590 --> 00:10:54,960
No V-neck either.

77
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:59,029
Refrain from wearing perfume
or manicuring your nails too.

78
00:11:00,700 --> 00:11:01,769
Yes, ma'am.

79
00:11:02,629 --> 00:11:05,299
(High school math)

80
00:11:10,809 --> 00:11:12,009
You scared me.

81
00:11:15,309 --> 00:11:17,080
When did you get here?
You were so quiet.

82
00:11:18,019 --> 00:11:19,450
Isn't my family annoying?

83
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:21,320
It is.

84
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,049
How come you don't quit then?

85
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:25,720
Your mom pays me a lot.

86
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:27,190
And I need that money.

87
00:11:27,759 --> 00:11:28,759
Open your book.

88
00:11:29,129 --> 00:11:30,330
I like it.

89
00:11:30,830 --> 00:11:31,860
Like what?

90
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:33,759
Everything my mom told you
not to do.

91
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:39,470
I like it too, but I won't do it.

92
00:11:40,399 --> 00:11:42,309
To me, one who pays me
is always right.

93
00:11:43,269 --> 00:11:47,279
So your taste doesn't
help me make a living.

94
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:48,809
Do you get it?

95
00:11:50,049 --> 00:11:51,779
It's page 16.

96
00:11:58,159 --> 00:12:01,629
(Kim Won)

97
00:12:09,629 --> 00:12:10,799
Page 15?

98
00:12:12,269 --> 00:12:13,370
Why aren't you answering?

99
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,509
We're in class. Look at the book.

100
00:12:15,570 --> 00:12:16,639
Is it your boyfriend?

101
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:18,139
It's integration by substitution.

102
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:26,279
Not rings. A necklace, please.

103
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,549
Necklace? Absolutely, sir.

104
00:12:28,549 --> 00:12:29,990
Please take a look right here.

105
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:34,429
- The wishbone?
- Absolutely, sir.

106
00:12:34,460 --> 00:12:35,730
Please show our guest.

107
00:12:40,159 --> 00:12:44,700
Sir. If I may say, this necklace
will make your dreams come true.

108
00:12:45,899 --> 00:12:48,570
What? That was the house deposit?

109
00:12:49,070 --> 00:12:50,909
Then where else would I
get such big money?

110
00:12:51,139 --> 00:12:53,539
I can't believe you.
Are you insane, Mom?

111
00:12:53,679 --> 00:12:55,480
How could you give it all to her?

112
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,379
She was lying about the wedding.

113
00:12:57,379 --> 00:12:59,980
I heard it. She called me.

114
00:13:00,549 --> 00:13:02,519
Crazy witch. How dare she call her?

115
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:05,419
What did she say?
Did she say it was all a lie?

116
00:13:06,019 --> 00:13:08,990
She said sorry
and asked if you're back safely.

117
00:13:09,759 --> 00:13:11,799
Is that all? Did you let it go?

118
00:13:12,429 --> 00:13:13,600
What if I don't?

119
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:16,129
What else can I do other than
hitting the phone?

120
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:17,970
So why did you give
all that money to her?

121
00:13:17,970 --> 00:13:20,799
That witch betrayed her mom
and sister to live well by herself.

122
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:22,070
Don't you get mad?

123
00:13:25,039 --> 00:13:27,279
Don't call your sister a witch.

124
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,250
What are we going to do now?

125
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:30,980
Are we going to live on streets?

126
00:13:33,919 --> 00:13:35,350
Wait here.

127
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:39,120
Why? For how long?

128
00:13:39,190 --> 00:13:40,320
How many minutes?

129
00:14:06,850 --> 00:14:07,850
It's me.

130
00:14:14,059 --> 00:14:17,159
Ms. Park. What's wrong with you?

131
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:21,029
Is spying on the first madam
going well?

132
00:14:21,129 --> 00:14:22,629
It was just the other day.

133
00:14:22,629 --> 00:14:24,370
What do you think?

134
00:14:26,940 --> 00:14:28,169
Do you trust me?

135
00:14:28,169 --> 00:14:29,639
What does that mean?

136
00:14:30,809 --> 00:14:33,340
My goodness. Am I being threatened?

137
00:14:36,279 --> 00:14:38,850
Yes. It hurts me too.

138
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,450
Seriously.

139
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:42,549
Who threatens with affection?

140
00:14:44,019 --> 00:14:45,220
What do you want?

141
00:14:46,419 --> 00:14:48,559
Madam. The first madam is here.

142
00:14:48,830 --> 00:14:50,759
What? Why all of a sudden?

143
00:14:52,730 --> 00:14:54,700
Did you tell her?

144
00:14:58,340 --> 00:15:01,070
Not yet, but since she's here...

145
00:15:03,840 --> 00:15:04,840
Wait.

146
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:08,750
What is it? Tell me what you want.

147
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:09,909
You have to tell...

148
00:15:11,149 --> 00:15:12,580
Write it.

149
00:15:17,049 --> 00:15:20,320
Put on something clean and neat.

150
00:15:20,789 --> 00:15:23,929
When did you change your socks?
Put on new socks.

151
00:15:24,059 --> 00:15:25,230
What are you doing?

152
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:30,629
This is where we're going to live
from now on.

153
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:34,710
What?

154
00:15:53,460 --> 00:15:57,360
What do you do
aside from wasting food?

155
00:15:57,730 --> 00:15:59,759
Why didn't you tell me
that the chairman is ill?

156
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:02,230
He's sick every other day.

157
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:04,539
How can I report it to you
every time?

158
00:16:05,169 --> 00:16:07,340
Do you want him to die or live?

159
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:09,740
What? What did you just say?

160
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,639
You shouldn't be doing this
in someone else's house...

161
00:16:11,639 --> 00:16:12,639
so early in the morning.

162
00:16:12,779 --> 00:16:15,750
- You're so energetic.
- What? Someone else's house?

163
00:16:16,179 --> 00:16:18,679
One who doesn't belong here is you.

164
00:16:19,049 --> 00:16:21,450
You're not even on the family
register. Watch your mouth.

165
00:16:21,919 --> 00:16:23,049
That stupid family register.

166
00:16:23,950 --> 00:16:25,259
You can't even give birth.

167
00:16:27,059 --> 00:16:28,529
You never disappoint me.

168
00:16:28,889 --> 00:16:30,190
"That stupid family register"?

169
00:16:30,190 --> 00:16:33,399
So is the child you gave birth to
with you right now?

170
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:35,399
- What?
- That's what family register is.

171
00:16:35,769 --> 00:16:37,669
You and I both don't have a child.

172
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:39,539
Life is long.

173
00:16:39,870 --> 00:16:41,110
Just because he's not with me now,

174
00:16:41,110 --> 00:16:42,669
doesn't mean he won't be
with me tomorrow.

175
00:16:43,009 --> 00:16:45,039
The blood is thicker than water
for a reason.

176
00:16:45,110 --> 00:16:47,340
- You...
- So, first madam.

177
00:16:47,679 --> 00:16:49,409
You need to manage your vigor well.

178
00:16:49,549 --> 00:16:51,779
Don't get dragged out when you get
kicked out of the family register.

179
00:16:51,779 --> 00:16:53,049
You should at least walk out on...

180
00:16:55,919 --> 00:16:57,019
I can't take it anymore.

181
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,289
Keep going. Say some more.

182
00:17:01,889 --> 00:17:02,889
Did you slap me?

183
00:17:04,089 --> 00:17:05,660
Did you just slap me?

184
00:17:05,759 --> 00:17:06,829
Can't you believe it?

185
00:17:07,329 --> 00:17:08,529
You want me to slap you again?

186
00:17:09,099 --> 00:17:10,299
Mr. Kim is coming.

187
00:17:22,650 --> 00:17:24,849
- You're home.
- You should go see your father.

188
00:17:24,849 --> 00:17:26,380
How was your business trip
to the US?

189
00:17:26,380 --> 00:17:27,519
You went to the US?

190
00:17:27,519 --> 00:17:28,619
I'm home.

191
00:17:29,049 --> 00:17:30,450
I'll let you guys chat.

192
00:17:31,259 --> 00:17:32,920
- Put the carry on in my room.
- Yes, sir.

193
00:17:39,529 --> 00:17:40,900
He wasn't home?

194
00:17:44,369 --> 00:17:45,599
Yes, life is long.

195
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:47,640
And blood is thicker than water.

196
00:17:49,039 --> 00:17:50,309
What are you talking about?

197
00:17:51,609 --> 00:17:54,910
Then did the chairman and Won
share water?

198
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:59,680
Let's see how well Tan will protect
his mom...

199
00:18:00,519 --> 00:18:01,519
against his brother.

200
00:18:14,529 --> 00:18:15,599
That witch.

201
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,799
She doesn't intimidate me at all.

202
00:18:19,869 --> 00:18:21,910
Ms. Park. Ice.

203
00:18:27,809 --> 00:18:30,480
Follow me. Bring medicine
to the chairman's room.

204
00:18:31,849 --> 00:18:32,849
Me?

205
00:19:13,259 --> 00:19:14,319
Hello.

206
00:19:14,930 --> 00:19:17,529
Mom went to do Madam's errand.

207
00:19:20,099 --> 00:19:23,430
Are you Ms. Park Hee Nam's daughter?

208
00:19:23,430 --> 00:19:24,470
Pardon?

209
00:19:25,740 --> 00:19:26,769
Yes.

210
00:19:34,009 --> 00:19:35,710
Why are you standing there
like that?

211
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:37,480
Sit down.

212
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,019
I have to go to work soon.

213
00:19:39,019 --> 00:19:41,420
What a lame excuse.

214
00:19:42,319 --> 00:19:43,390
I met Tan.

215
00:19:43,519 --> 00:19:48,029
I know people who went to the party
better than you do.

216
00:19:48,430 --> 00:19:49,559
But...

217
00:19:50,059 --> 00:19:52,500
no one talked about Tan.

218
00:19:53,930 --> 00:19:57,170
You should rescind
your brother's exile now.

219
00:19:58,839 --> 00:20:00,240
Or I will.

220
00:20:01,809 --> 00:20:04,369
I understand your pain.

221
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,839
So, to be fair,

222
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:10,279
I turned a blind eye
to you hurting Tan.

223
00:20:12,079 --> 00:20:13,079
But...

224
00:20:14,890 --> 00:20:17,349
you're taking it way too far.

225
00:20:17,890 --> 00:20:19,559
That's not fair.

226
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,759
Is making the weight of pain
the same...

227
00:20:22,460 --> 00:20:24,529
your idea of fairness?

228
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,000
I have...

229
00:20:28,099 --> 00:20:32,500
never hugged Tan
because you might hate it.

230
00:20:34,569 --> 00:20:35,640
I think...

231
00:20:36,470 --> 00:20:38,109
I'd end up regretting.

232
00:20:38,140 --> 00:20:39,380
That sounds like...

233
00:20:40,180 --> 00:20:42,210
you raised me with love.

234
00:20:43,579 --> 00:20:45,880
Are you sure you wouldn't
regret anything about me?

235
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:46,950
Do you think...

236
00:20:48,220 --> 00:20:50,289
I'm asking for your opinion?

237
00:20:52,819 --> 00:20:53,920
I'll get going.

238
00:21:03,769 --> 00:21:05,039
She's ridiculous.

239
00:21:05,500 --> 00:21:07,869
Neither of us is a good wife.

240
00:21:11,839 --> 00:21:14,750
I know. There's even a book
about it.

241
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:16,579
"You're a Concubine
Because It Hurts".

242
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:17,750
What?

243
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:25,589
Doesn't this family look ridiculous,
even to you?

244
00:21:27,589 --> 00:21:29,390
You must be happy since you're poor.

245
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:31,089
You wouldn't have to deal with this.

246
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,630
Well, that can't be the reason.

247
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:38,740
Hold on.

248
00:21:39,299 --> 00:21:42,640
If Won went to the US,
he must've met Tan.

249
00:21:47,809 --> 00:21:48,980
I'm going in.

250
00:21:53,779 --> 00:21:56,049
If you're going to the US,
you should've...

251
00:21:56,049 --> 00:21:57,849
Ask Father if it's about Tan.

252
00:21:58,859 --> 00:22:00,289
Did you meet Tan?

253
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,789
What did he say? Is he doing well?

254
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:05,500
Is he all right? Did he ask you
about me?

255
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:07,059
Don't you know his phone number?

256
00:22:07,359 --> 00:22:08,529
You want me to give it to you?

257
00:22:08,529 --> 00:22:10,470
He never picks up.

258
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:14,000
Right. Let me ask you
since we're on the topic.

259
00:22:14,369 --> 00:22:16,509
Until when will you stop Tan
from coming to Korea?

260
00:22:16,670 --> 00:22:18,680
Do you have to be this mean?

261
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,380
What did an 18-year-old do so...

262
00:22:20,380 --> 00:22:22,509
I was an heir to Jeguk Group
at that age.

263
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:25,319
I was a major stockholder
with eight percent of voting right.

264
00:22:27,019 --> 00:22:29,319
Fine. Then I take it back.

265
00:22:32,460 --> 00:22:33,559
But Won,

266
00:22:35,059 --> 00:22:37,160
I'm too ashamed to see Tan.

267
